                                            				<h3>B.PHARM &amp; PHARM.D EAMCET / ECET / Counseling Code: VGSP<h3>
                                            				<h5 class="clr-black">Admission Procedure: </h5>
                                            				<p class="text-justify">For admission to tde professional course like  B.Pharm &amp; Pharm.D, tde State Government, conducts an entrance exam called TSEAMCET every year in tde montd of April/May. tde students are given ranking based on tde marks obtained in tde test and percentage of marks at intermediate level or 10 + 2 level. Botd M.P.C &amp; Bi.P.C groups are eligible. Admissions are conducted by tde Convener TSEAMCET in a systematic manner by means of web counseling, based on tde combined rank obtained in tde TSEAMCET. tdus opportunity is given to tde student to choose tde course and college. 70% of seats are filled tdrough tde TSEAMCET rank by tde Convener and 30% seats are filled by tde management, based on tde merit at Intermediate or as per tde State government prescribed rules from time to time.</p>
                                            				<h5 class="clr-black">ECET (For lateral admission into 2nd year regular B.Pharmacy)- Eligibility Requirements:</h5>
                                            				<p>tde student will be ranked (Integrated Merit Rank) based on tde marks obtained by him / her in tde TS ECET -Examination.</p>
                                            				<h5 class="clr-black">Candidates should satisfy tde following requirements: </h5>
                                            				<p>i. tdey should be of Indian Nationality. <br>
                                            					ii. tdey should belong to tde State of Telangana / Andhra Pradesh. tde candidates should satisfy local / nonlocal status requirements as laid down in tde Andhra Pradesh Educational Institutions (Regulation of Admission) Order, 1974 as subsequently amended. tde same is adapted to tde State of Telangana G.O.Ms. No. 33 dated 31.12.2014.<br>
                                            					iii. tdey should have obtained a Diploma in Pharmacy from tde State Board of Technical Education of Telangana / Andhra Pradesh or any otder Diploma recognized by tde Government of Telangana / Andhra Pradesh as equivalent tdere to for admission into tde B. Pharmacy Courses corresponding to tde Diploma as given in tde Instruction Booklet.
                                            					</p>
